{
  "texts": [
    "One recurring problem an ecommerce platform found was a significant number of customers stopping their search sessions without making a purchase.",
    "Even with a huge range of products, consumers often battled to find their preferred ones, sometimes because of conflicting or inconsistent search results.The company rebuilt their search engine using llMs.",
    "Instead of relying only on keyword matching, they used semantic search enabled by rapid integration with a language model.",
    "The questions were meant to help a user determine the reason for their search & provide matching answers.",
    "When a user searches \"shoes for standing all day,\" for instance, traditional search engines could provide an odd mix of sandals and sneakers."
  ]
}